annotation.TEXT: Looks like this hack gets an "A"! ...Or maybe it wants me to press "A" to spin jump off of these guys.
And, welcome to... :P :P :P! Or you can call it "P P P", or "Colon-P Colon-P Colon-P", or "Phbbbbt Phbbbbt Phbbbbt"!
Alright, here we go! That Thwomp can pass through the "M" blocks, so I've gotta shield myself by standing under other blocks at the right times!
To be continued... :P
Oh, man. How nasty is this gonna get when I flip this switch?
Looks like there's gonna be more ON/OFF switch and Thwomp shenanigans here.

Can't reach those ? blocks... Well, maybe I could, but I'm most likely gonna come back here later after hitting a switch to toggle the ! blocks, so I can hit them then. Also, these Thwomps aren't moving for some reason.
Hi, Yoshi!
Umm... Can I maybe get back to the normal paths, or am I totally stuck?
Whoa, super-ultra-mega-large fire bar there.
And now the Yellow Switch Palace is visible.

Oh, what? That guy's still awake? Well that sucks... Oh! I just realized something. The purple coins indicated a Thwomp that moves while the switch is OFF, and the orange coins indicated a Thwomp that moves while the switch is ON. Also, the yellow coins indicated that jerk who's always awake regardless of the switch.
Sacrificial horse count: 1
Well, at least I only got hit once, but it seems like you'd have to be ultra fast to avoid taking damage there...
Doing alright so far... Oh, god, what is this?
BGM: Mother - Introduction

Hey, there's some more Thwomps, which are totally trapped. This ON/OFF switch doesn't seem to affect them, but it's probably there just to make sure the switch is OFF to begin the next section. Also, zwee, and I'll certainly take that flower.
Well, there's Vanilla Secret... Squiggly... with a black hole to the right of it. (It's "Vanilla Secret Yu" according to TheGoomba98.)
Oh, well this isn't so bad, and I like that I don't have to ever worry about not landing on the Thwomp, since he's always locked on to me.
Okay, now for the next part, I guess I gotta hit that turn block just after the Thwomp stomps it, then run like mad!
Yep, they're totally awake now!
Yeah, I think I'm stuck. Gimme a moment, folks...
Argh! Wow, I wasn't nearly fast enough there.

Sorry, but I don't understand your moonspeak, nor this message box's moonspeak. (If anyone can translate these for me, that would be nice.) (UPDATE: Zeldara109 thinks that the message that appeared with Yoshi may have been a Yoshi sound effect.)
Goal tape average so far: 40 / 1 = 40 stars each.
BGM: Zelda series - Main Theme
Unfortunately, it seems that this Thwomp is immune to tossed ice blocks. (That would've been so cheesy if I could've killed it that way, though!)
I was thinking of being silly and picking file B or C this time, but... nah. We'll go with A like usual.
Ooh, a 1-up!
...Umm... I don't think that was supposed to happen...
So, are these Thwomps asleep or something? And, what's with these "S" blocks? ...Oh, I think I know, and I'm pretty sure I know why the Thwomps are asleep and what will wake them up...
I wonder why some of these coins are different colors... Maybe just to show the different Thwomp paths?
Alright, I've let the unedited demo go through one full loop while listening to this Mother music, so let's get this game started!
Anything hidden to the left of the pipe? ...Doesn't look like it. Then I'm going up.
I guess he's stomping downward, so it's perfectly safe to get this Yoshi coin.
Well, at least I get another feather.
Okay, there we go. (Wow, I haven't even entered any levels yet and I've already had to use a rewind.) So, can I also climb up to where the Yellow Switch Palace would normally be? ...Yep.
Oh, man. When I hit this switch...
Awesome, there's the goal. Well, this level was pretty neat. If I missed any secrets here, let me know!
Gotta hit that switch while this guy is down low.
Aw, what? I guess I can't enter this pipe with Yoshi. Well, bye, Yoshi!
Spikes do!
Now, the "S" blocks are blocks that only Mario can pass through. For other sprites, they act like solid blocks. (So, maybe the "S" stands for "sprites".)
...Huh, there's no "number of players" choice in this hack.
I've gotta quickly move over, grab an ice block, then retreat back to the previous safe spot. Although, maybe I could've just gone through all 4 ice blocks in one fell swoop...
The cape makes this pretty easy.
Uh, oh. There's poison, too!
Alright, now I think I'll go to this fortress here, where Yoshi's Island 1 would normally be. (This level is called Switch Thwomp's Fortress.)

(Oh, and if you don't think "Phbbbbt" is the correct spelling for a raspberry noise, try Google searching "raspberry noise spelling" and then tell me in the comments how you think it should be spelled.)
And, I guess I go back in the pipe I originally came out of here.
What lies beneath?

However, I'm just gonna stick with these levels down here for now. Let's begin with Yoshi's House. (If anyone knows what these level names actually say, let me know! This one is indeed Yoshi's House.)
Watch out for the Maverick Thwomps that are here, too.
By the way, is ":P :P :P" the hack-maker's real name? (TheGoomba98 says yes.)
Oh, and yes, I am aware that raocow has LP-ed this hack (which was over five years ago), but I'm going to play this anyway.
Alright, a noble spirit mushroom, which embiggens the smallest Mario.

Alright, so we've got SMW's original overworld, but with some edits here and there, and I can either go to Yoshi's House, or the fortress to the left, or the ghost house to the right... Or, travel along unrevealed paths right now...
BGM: Donkey Kong Country 2 - Krook's March
Well, I guess I'll eat these berries.
Huh, a flower. Well, I'll certainly take it, but who knows if fireballs will be good for anything here.
Looks like we're doing some more ON/OFF switch stuff.
Good to know. Also, I got all of the Yoshi coins, which is cool.
BARF! I totally screwed that up.

Alright, this properly opens the path leading to the Yellow Switch Palace (which really is called Yellow Switch Palace). Also, I notice that the black circle to the right of the level name now shows a coin. I guess that indicates that I got all of the Yoshi coins.

Conversely, I'm pretty sure those "M" blocks at the start are the opposite way-- solid only for Mario, and pass-throughable for other sprites, which is why Yoshi fell to his doom when I dismounted him back there.
I had no problem dodging those Thwomps. Now to hit those other ? blocks.
There's some more "M" blocks, which are solid for me, but not for the Thwomps.
Oh, geez. What's this game gonna demand of me next?
Of course, the Yellow Switch Palace isn't actually visible yet, but I'm sure I could enter it right now if I wanted.
I'll take that extra mushroom, thank you very much.
Whoops... I wasn't expecting Yoshi to fall through those "M" blocks like that. Oh, well.

I like how this level shows you how the "M" blocks work before you get into a situation where you could be taken by surprise, so if you get hit by this Thwomp, then it's your own darn fault for not paying attention.
Whoa! That one's awake! Well, I guess that's something I've gotta watch out for.
Oh, geez. What's this? That Thwomp up there is totally locked on to me, and I can definitely see what I'm going to have to go through once I hit an ON/OFF switch...
OMNOMNOM...
I can still spin jump on them while they're like this, right? ...Yep.
Well, :P to you too!
Oh, boy. Yoshi's tongue is glitchy-looking. Yay.

So, should I play the Yellow Switch Palace next? Or should I head to this ghost house where YI2 would normally be? Or should I walk along the unrevealed paths and go elsewhere next? Place your votes now!
I don't think this room is quite as tricky as the previous one. I just made a dumb mistake there.
Space-time rewind count: 1
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x, sticking his tongue out three times for some reason!
Ooh, feather!

This was, well... not directly suggested to me, but Blue Yoshi 815 wanted to give me a challenge for this hack. However, while I'm not actually accepting challenges for hacks, I was interested in just simply doing a playthrough of this hack, so here you go!
